Hi @Rsasbrink!

It sounds like you need add a specific parser for that column... It doesn't have a radio parser included, but you should still load in the [`parser-input-select.js`](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/parsers/parser-input-select.js) file to handle automatically updating the cache when the content changes. Then include the following parser, and set it in the appointment column:

HTML

```html
<th class="sorter-radio">Appointment status</th>
```

Script

```js
$.tablesorter.addParser({
	id : 'radio',
	is : function() {
		return false;
	},
	format : function( txt, table, cell ) {
		var $input = $( cell ).find( 'input:checked' );
		return $input.length ? $input.val() : txt;
	},
	parsed : true, // filter widget flag
	type : 'text'
});
```

