@ricci: I pushed out recent changes. It is one if-statement in `post_config_hook` to avoid skipping the last state for `xfce4-notify`. Now I wonder if that was a mistake... because it seems you want it off on system reboots? Otherwise, I'm not sure if we can differentiate i3 restarts vs system reboots.

Did you thought the module thought it was on because of the last state or did you check with `xfce4` command too? The module will set the last state too in `post_config_hook`.. so maybe when you turns it on, reboots, and it sets the last state... so you thought it was not right? Can you check this?

@maximbaz Can you explain more about resetting? `do_not_disturb` is trying to survive between restarts so the last state is the last state.. and it checks every 20 seconds.

