@ogrisel: this has nothing to do with the patchelf version, and nothing to do with the manylinux docker image. AFAICT there are two bugs here:

(1) the auditwheel tests here fetch the 'pypatchelf' package from pypi, which is a Python wrapper for patchelf, and the wrapper breaks `patchelf --version`. ([pypatchelf fix is here](https://github.com/rmcgibbo/pypatchelf/pull/1)). And since `patchelf --version` is broken, auditwheel's attempt to check the `patchelf` version is also broken. The fix for this is just to merge that PR on pypatchelf and release a new version on PyPI.

(2) (this bug) Somehow the test suite here is "passing", even though it's full of unhandled exception tracebacks. This seems like a bug in the test suite, since generally unhandled exceptions should trigger a test failure.

