I am beginning to be able to articulate @thobrla concerns from #545 now after trying to implement this.

Instead of `self._properties.get('contentType')` I made two failed attempts:

- `self.content_type`: Fails because `_reload_properties()` was called (gave a 404 when the object didn't exist or failed for more spectacular reasons when I used a fake connection)
- `self.properties.get('contentType')`: Again fails because `properties` itself calls `_reload_properties` when `self._properties` is False-y.

I think we have to ditch the majority of uses of `_reload_properties`

Here are the two culprits (as of f73ad7e8fc877e14e2f9c0b4ec42430f2396f770) I mentioned:

```python
def _scalar_property(fieldname):
    def _getter(self):
        return self.properties[fieldname]

class _PropertyMixin(object):
    @property
    def properties(self):
        if not self._properties:
            self._reload_properties()
        return self._properties.copy()
```

