We may add interfaces to dispatch the CoAP message to Application process if it shares the Thread Management port(:MM) with TMF in core in the future (as in 10.6.3).
But currently OT core only processes TMF CoAP message which meets the stricter rules in this PR (also meet with the rules in 10.6.2), and simply drops CoAP messages which doesn't meet the rules.

Yes, we cannot route ML-EIDs. But we are not 'switching to RLOCs' via replacing ML-EID with RLOC in IP layer. Instead,  6LowPAN Mesh Header would be added for routing in mesh if the destination is not the direct neighbor. (5.10.1.1). 
Lower layer should not modify the IP header,  but only forward the IP packet (if routable) or drop it (if not routable)

@jwhui ,  just as @thcu-gp points out, if the CoAP message has ML-EID as both source and dest address, it doesn't meet with TMF addressing rules in 10.6.2. Then it should be all right for OT stack to not process such CoAP message.

